34% did it in high school.

00:02:41.523 --> 00:02:43.126
I don’t believe it!
There’s no way

00:02:43.159 --> 00:02:44.896
that many teens have
crossed that threshold!

00:02:44.930 --> 00:02:46.399
[narrator] <i>34%!</i>

00:02:46.432 --> 00:02:48.771
<i>Over a third have tasted</i>
<i>the forbidden fruit,</i>

00:02:48.804 --> 00:02:51.242
<i>which means that</i>
<i>in a class of 30 students,</i>

00:02:51.275 --> 00:02:52.946
<i>10 have already done it.</i>

00:02:52.979 --> 00:02:56.185
<i>And statistically, so has</i>
<i>one of the three in this room.</i>

00:02:56.219 --> 00:02:58.223
[Fujiwara] I bet it’s
higher than it should be

00:02:58.256 --> 00:02:59.993
because the only people
who took the survey

00:03:00.027 --> 00:03:01.797
are the ones
who like to read this stuff.

00:03:01.830 --> 00:03:04.368
[Shirogane] Right.
It’s the sample selection bias.

00:03:04.402 --> 00:03:07.074
That number’s way too high
to be accurate.

00:03:07.107 --> 00:03:08.677
Oh, for sure.

00:03:08.711 --> 00:03:09.980
[both laugh]

00:03:10.013 --> 00:03:10.982
[Shinomiya] You think so?

00:03:11.015 --> 00:03:13.654
34% seems accurate enough to me.

00:03:13.687 --> 00:03:15.023
‐ [gasps]
‐ Eh?

00:03:15.057 --> 00:03:17.327
Actually it’s rather low.

00:03:17.361 --> 00:03:20.702
Okay, so I’m fairly positive
the answer’s no,

00:03:20.735 --> 00:03:24.241
