00:11:12.010 --> 00:11:15.751
Although 20 questions almost
seems too easy, don’t you think?

00:11:15.784 --> 00:11:17.588
Especially for someone
who understands me

00:11:17.622 --> 00:11:18.590
as well as you do.

00:11:18.624 --> 00:11:20.093
So why don’t we halve that

00:11:20.126 --> 00:11:22.397
and give you 10 questions
to get it right?

00:11:22.430 --> 00:11:24.268
Fine by me.

00:11:24.301 --> 00:11:26.171
You’re on.

00:11:28.309 --> 00:11:29.913
Shall we start?

00:11:29.946 --> 00:11:30.915
We shall.

00:11:30.948 --> 00:11:33.052
[Western music playing]

00:11:35.958 --> 00:11:38.697
[Shirogane]
Ten questions, it is.

00:11:38.730 --> 00:11:41.736
One, have you chosen
something tangible?

00:11:41.770 --> 00:11:45.076
Yes. It isn’t merely a word
or a concept.

00:11:45.109 --> 00:11:47.380
Two, is it
an electrical appliance?

00:11:47.414 --> 00:11:48.382
No.

00:11:48.416 --> 00:11:50.353
Three, would you consider it

00:11:50.386 --> 00:11:52.290
to be significantly warm
or cold?

00:11:52.324 --> 00:11:53.292
Yes.

00:11:53.326 --> 00:11:54.696
Hmm.

00:11:54.729 --> 00:11:56.533
<i>Considering her answers,</i>

00:11:56.566 --> 00:11:58.670
<i>it could be</i>
<i>some kind of animal,</i>

00:11:58.704 --> 00:12:01.676
<i>food, hot water, ice,</i>

00:12:01.710 --> 00:12:04.916
<i>fire, or a myriad</i>
<i>of other things.</i>

00:12:04.949 --> 00:12:07.722
<i>However, since this is meant</i>

00:12:07.755 --> 00:12:09.993
<i>to test my understanding</i>
<i>of Shinomiya,</i>

00:12:10.026 --> 00:12:13.332
<i>the answer must be connected</i>
<i>to her somehow,</i>

00:12:13.366 --> 00:12:14.836
<i>which means...</i>

00:12:14.869 --> 00:12:19.812
Four, is this thing
a possession of yours?

00:12:19.846 --> 00:12:20.981
‐ No.
‐ [gunshot]

00:12:21.015 --> 00:12:24.388
Five, is it something
you touched today?

00:12:24.421 --> 00:12:25.390
‐ No.
‐ [gunshot]

00:12:25.423 --> 00:12:28.797
Then six, could I find it
at your house right now?

00:12:28.830 --> 00:12:30.400
‐ No.
‐ [bullet ricochets]

00:12:30.433 --> 00:12:32.972
<i>That makes three noes in a row.</i>

00:12:33.005 --> 00:12:36.245
<i>I thought it would be</i>
<i>some trinket of hers,</i>

00:12:36.278 --> 00:12:39.017
<i>but I guess I was wrong.</i>

00:12:39.051 --> 00:12:42.057
<i>I’ll just have to explore</i>
<i>her mind further.</i>

00:12:42.090 --> 00:12:43.961
Okay, seven,

00:12:43.994 --> 00:12:45.731
do you happen
to like this thing?

00:12:45.764 --> 00:12:49.204
[gunshot echoes]

00:12:49.237 --> 00:12:50.507
I do.

00:12:50.541 --> 00:12:52.143
[sighs]

00:12:52.177 --> 00:12:55.517
<i>What the hell’s</i>
<i>with that face?!</i>

00:12:55.551 --> 00:12:57.788
<i>She is blushing,</i>
<i>full‐on blushing!</i>

00:12:57.822 --> 00:12:59.024
<i>Does that mean</i>
<i>she’s embarrassed?</i>

00:12:59.057 --> 00:13:02.430
<i>Why would she</i>
<i>be embarrassed unless..</i>

00:13:02.464 --> 00:13:04.769
[wind blows]

00:13:04.802 --> 00:13:06.038
<i>unless...</i>

00:13:06.071 --> 00:13:09.144
Eight, might this be
a living thing?

00:13:09.177 --> 00:13:10.146
[gunshot]

00:13:10.179 --> 00:13:12.150
[gasps]

00:13:13.052 --> 00:13:15.557
[sighs] Yes, it’s alive.

00:13:15.591 --> 00:13:17.928
<i>I was right.</i>

00:13:17.962 --> 00:13:20.567
<i>It’s me.</i>
<i>She’s talking about me.</i>

00:13:20.601 --> 00:13:23.239
<i>Okay, calm down</i>
<i>and get it together.</i>

00:13:23.272 --> 00:13:25.443
<i>You need to confirm.</i>

00:13:25.476 --> 00:13:26.746
<i>I’m something tangible.</i>

00:13:26.780 --> 00:13:28.015
<i>I’m not</i>
<i>an electrical appliance.</i>

00:13:28.049 --> 00:13:29.418
<i>I’m relatively warm.</i>

00:13:29.451 --> 00:13:32.658
<i>Shinomiya doesn’t own me,</i>
<i>nor has she touched me today,</i>

00:13:32.692 --> 00:13:34.662
<i>and I’m obviously</i>
<i>not in her house.</i>

00:13:34.696 --> 00:13:36.231
<i>It all matches.</i>

00:13:36.265 --> 00:13:39.404
<i>Then there’s the part</i>
<i>about her liking the thing.</i>

00:13:39.438 --> 00:13:41.509
<i>Hold on.</i>

00:13:41.543 --> 00:13:43.580
<i>Is this</i>
<i>a roundabout confession?</i>

00:13:45.584 --> 00:13:46.553
’M‐kay,

00:13:46.586 --> 00:13:47.688
nine, tell me,

00:13:47.722 --> 00:13:50.326
in what way do you
like this thing?

00:13:50.360 --> 00:13:52.163
Uh, as a good friend?

00:13:52.197 --> 00:13:53.232
As a human?

00:13:53.265 --> 00:13:54.502
Or as more maybe?

00:13:56.506 --> 00:13:57.908
I can’t answer that.

00:13:57.942 --> 00:14:00.881
Remember, you can only ask me
yes‐or‐no questions.

00:14:02.050 --> 00:14:03.152
<i>Crap!</i>

00:14:03.185 --> 00:14:05.824
<i>I got so worked up</i>
<i>that I wasted a shot!</i>

00:14:05.858 --> 00:14:07.528
<i>It’s fine. Keep your head.</i>

00:14:07.561 --> 00:14:11.335
<i>There’s still a chance</i>
<i>that you’re missing something.</i>

00:14:11.368 --> 00:14:14.876
All right, last question.

00:14:14.909 --> 00:14:17.681
Is it something
both intelligent and handsome,

00:14:17.715 --> 00:14:21.055
with piercing eyes
and blondish hair?

00:14:21.088 --> 00:14:23.960
[sighs]

00:14:26.866 --> 00:14:27.935
Mm‐hmm.

00:14:30.473 --> 00:14:32.043
<i>It’s me!</i>

00:14:32.077 --> 00:14:33.847
[theme music playing]

00:14:33.880 --> 00:14:37.120
<i>It’s me. It’s really me.</i>

00:14:37.153 --> 00:14:39.859
<i>You are something else.</i>

00:14:39.892 --> 00:14:43.466
<i>Thinking up such</i>
<i>a roundabout way to confess.</i>

00:14:43.499 --> 00:14:45.303
<i>It’s been a long war.</i>

00:14:45.336 --> 00:14:48.109
<i>We put each other</i>
<i>through a lot.</i>

00:14:48.142 --> 00:14:52.317
<i>But it’s thanks to those</i>
<i>trying times that I finally...</i>

00:14:52.350 --> 00:14:54.555
‐ [music slows, stops]
‐ <i>understand...</i>

00:14:54.589 --> 00:14:56.191
<i>you.</i>

00:14:58.830 --> 00:15:00.433
[sighs]

00:15:00.466 --> 00:15:03.038
That was your tenth question,
President.

00:15:04.241 --> 00:15:06.746
Can you guess
what I’m thinking of?

00:15:06.780 --> 00:15:09.217
<i>I think I can.</i>

00:15:09.251 --> 00:15:12.457
<i>I do know what kind of person</i>
<i>you are to an extent.</i>

00:15:13.994 --> 00:15:15.564
<i>And, well...</i>

00:15:15.597 --> 00:15:16.866
My answer is...

00:15:16.900 --> 00:15:18.369
[gasps]

00:15:19.605 --> 00:15:20.674
a dog.

00:15:20.707 --> 00:15:22.177
[groans]

00:15:22.210 --> 00:15:25.116
Congratulations.
You did it. Yay.

00:15:25.149 --> 00:15:28.055
[Shirogane] Specifically
Fujiwara’s dog, Pesu.

00:15:28.088 --> 00:15:30.293
[Shinomiya]
Shall we go home now?

00:15:30.326 --> 00:15:32.397
It’s getting pretty late
after all.

00:15:33.499 --> 00:15:35.403
Uh, good point.

00:15:39.344 --> 00:15:41.883
[narrator] <i>Results</i>
<i>for today’s test,</i>

00:15:41.916 --> 00:15:43.653
<i>he passes.</i>

00:15:52.738 --> 00:15:54.007
[narrator] <i>Once again,</i>

00:15:54.040 --> 00:15:56.011
<i>Kaguya’s part</i>
<i>of the Shinomiya family,</i>

00:15:56.044 --> 00:15:58.817
<i>one of Japan’s leading</i>
<i>business conglomerates.</i>

00:15:58.850 --> 00:16:00.721
<i>Her life</i>
<i>was planned out for her</i>

00:16:00.754 --> 00:16:02.223
<i>from the day she was born.</i>

00:16:02.257 --> 00:16:05.731
<i>She doesn’t often get</i>
<i>to enjoy the freedom to choose,</i>

00:16:05.764 --> 00:16:07.433
<i>not even for trivial things.</i>

00:16:07.467 --> 00:16:09.806
‐ [kids chatting]
‐ ...got free ice cream.

00:16:09.839 --> 00:16:13.914
<i>2,574, that’s</i>
<i>the number of times</i>

00:16:13.947 --> 00:16:15.951
<i>she’s gazed out</i>
<i>of a fancy car’s window</i>

00:16:15.984 --> 00:16:17.253
<i>on the way to school.</i>

00:16:18.355 --> 00:16:19.826
[birds chirping]

00:16:19.859 --> 00:16:21.529
<i>But then, one day...</i>

00:16:21.563 --> 00:16:22.832
Is that a cat?

00:16:22.865 --> 00:16:25.036
‐ [growls]
‐ Yes.

00:16:25.069 --> 00:16:28.442
It unfortunately lodged itself
in there fairly deep.

00:16:28.475 --> 00:16:30.714
Please allow me
just a few more minutes.

00:16:30.747 --> 00:16:33.285
I’ll arrange for another car
to take you to school.

00:16:33.319 --> 00:16:35.891
It’s all right. I’d rather walk
than wait around.

00:16:35.924 --> 00:16:38.162
At least let Hayasaka
go with you.

00:16:38.195 --> 00:16:40.333
Sure, I can do that.

00:16:41.435 --> 00:16:42.738
[gasps]

00:16:42.771 --> 00:16:45.644
But I would have
to change clothes first.

00:16:45.677 --> 00:16:47.013
She’d wind up being late.

00:16:47.046 --> 00:16:49.351
I think she can manage
walking to school by herself.

00:16:49.384 --> 00:16:51.556
You see? Nothing to worry about.

00:16:51.589 --> 00:16:52.725
I’ll be fine.

00:16:52.758 --> 00:16:54.862
Uh, but, Lady Kaguya!

00:16:54.896 --> 00:16:56.599
I’ll see you later.

00:16:56.633 --> 00:16:57.668
[laughs]

00:16:59.237 --> 00:17:00.172
[sighs]

00:17:00.206 --> 00:17:02.143
[narrator]
<i>The morning sun is shining</i>

00:17:02.176 --> 00:17:04.782
<i>a little brighter than usual</i>
<i>for Kaguya today.</i>

00:17:04.815 --> 00:17:07.287
[gate creaks]

00:17:08.823 --> 00:17:11.529
[peaceful music playing]

00:17:18.643 --> 00:17:20.379
<i>All right, this might just be</i>

00:17:20.413 --> 00:17:23.285
<i>the only chance I ever get</i>
<i>to go to school on foot,</i>

00:17:23.319 --> 00:17:26.024
<i>so I’m going to milk it</i>
<i>for all it’s worth.</i>

00:17:26.058 --> 00:17:27.126
<i>Let’s see.</i>

00:17:27.160 --> 00:17:28.530
<i>If I recall, the President</i>

00:17:28.563 --> 00:17:30.534
<i>rides his bike to school</i>
<i>from Setagaya,</i>

00:17:30.567 --> 00:17:33.372
<i>which means Meiji Street</i>
<i>is probably the route he takes.</i>

00:17:33.405 --> 00:17:35.877
<i>He barely makes it</i>
<i>by the time the bell rings,</i>

00:17:35.911 --> 00:17:37.313
<i>so if I wait by the bridge,</i>

00:17:37.347 --> 00:17:39.552
<i>I’m almost positive</i>
<i>our paths will cross.</i>

00:17:42.490 --> 00:17:44.160
[chuckling]

00:17:48.970 --> 00:17:51.074
[crying]

00:17:53.580 --> 00:17:55.082
[crying continues]

00:17:58.757 --> 00:18:01.461
I better hurry, or I won’t
catch the president in time.

00:18:08.777 --> 00:18:11.081
[sighs] What’s wrong?

00:18:12.016 --> 00:18:13.520
If you’re
in some sort of trouble,

00:18:13.553 --> 00:18:16.491
sum it up
as concisely as you can.

00:18:17.661 --> 00:18:20.166
It’s the crosswalk.

00:18:20.199 --> 00:18:21.502
What about it?

00:18:25.644 --> 00:18:27.046
Here. Take my hand.

00:18:27.080 --> 00:18:28.950
I’ll cross it
side by side with you.

00:18:28.984 --> 00:18:30.086
[girl whimpers]

00:18:31.388 --> 00:18:33.292
[beeping]

00:18:36.799 --> 00:18:38.837
[gasps]

00:18:38.870 --> 00:18:41.308
Okay. You can let go of me now.

00:18:43.112 --> 00:18:46.819
There are more, more crosswalks
on my way to school.

00:18:46.853 --> 00:18:49.024
[groans]

00:18:49.057 --> 00:18:51.228
[peaceful music playing]

00:18:55.102 --> 00:18:56.171
[Shinomiya] I’m curious.

00:18:56.204 --> 00:18:58.510
How were you getting to school
before today?

00:18:59.845 --> 00:19:01.448
We had walking groups.

00:19:01.481 --> 00:19:05.657
Yeti was the one who always
held my hand when we crossed.

00:19:05.691 --> 00:19:07.393
Like the Abominable Snowman?

00:19:07.427 --> 00:19:09.164
Yeah. It’s her nickname.

00:19:09.197 --> 00:19:11.368
Her real names Ienaga.

00:19:11.401 --> 00:19:14.274
But now that we graduated
to the upper grades,

00:19:14.307 --> 00:19:16.813
we don’t walk to school
in groups anymore,

00:19:16.846 --> 00:19:18.650
so I’m on my own.

00:19:22.190 --> 00:19:24.562
[stifled crying]

00:19:24.595 --> 00:19:26.164
[sobbing]

00:19:26.198 --> 00:19:27.701
<i>She may have</i>
<i>physically advanced,</i>

00:19:27.735 --> 00:19:29.638
<i>but her mind is still</i>
<i>that of an infant’s.</i>

00:19:29.672 --> 00:19:31.709
<i>I definitely had</i>
<i>a better head on my shoulders</i>

00:19:31.743 --> 00:19:32.644
<i>when I was her age.</i>

00:19:37.921 --> 00:19:39.759
I don’t wanna be alone!

00:19:39.792 --> 00:19:41.763
Yeti should be with me!

00:19:41.796 --> 00:19:43.700
‐ [crying]
‐ [gasps]

00:19:47.508 --> 00:19:49.177
Listen.

00:19:49.210 --> 00:19:50.446
Just because
you aren’t officially

00:19:50.479 --> 00:19:52.150
walking to school
in groups anymore

00:19:52.183 --> 00:19:54.755
doesn’t mean
you have to go alone.

00:19:54.789 --> 00:19:55.690
Hmm?

00:19:56.826 --> 00:19:57.828
You should try meeting friends

00:19:57.861 --> 00:20:00.066
somewhere in between
or at each other’s houses.

00:20:00.099 --> 00:20:02.771
Then you can walk together
just like you want.

00:20:02.805 --> 00:20:04.107
Right?

00:20:04.140 --> 00:20:06.879
[gasps] That’s a great idea!

00:20:06.913 --> 00:20:08.182
You’re some kind of genius?

00:20:08.215 --> 00:20:10.987
[laughs] Sometimes.

00:20:11.021 --> 00:20:12.691
[girl] Mikiti!

00:20:12.725 --> 00:20:13.860
[Mikiti laughs]

00:20:13.893 --> 00:20:14.795
Hey, Yeti!

00:20:16.098 --> 00:20:19.505
Well, what are you
waiting for? Go on.

00:20:19.538 --> 00:20:20.306
’Kay.

00:20:20.339 --> 00:20:21.475
[signal beeping]

00:20:21.509 --> 00:20:24.114
Thank you for helping me,
genius lady!

00:20:24.147 --> 00:20:26.619
[laughs]

00:20:26.652 --> 00:20:28.355
[Yeti] Were you
surprised to see me?

00:20:28.388 --> 00:20:30.126
Yeah, but in a good way.

00:20:30.159 --> 00:20:31.394
[laughter]

00:20:31.428 --> 00:20:33.132
[Mikiti] Walking together
is more fun.

00:20:33.165 --> 00:20:34.367
Uh‐huh!

00:20:34.400 --> 00:20:37.206
Right. Now where am I?

00:20:41.849 --> 00:20:43.385
8:25.

00:20:43.419 --> 00:20:45.322
No way I’ll make it.

00:20:46.458 --> 00:20:47.828
[sighs]

00:20:47.861 --> 00:20:49.431
If they find out I was late,

00:20:49.464 --> 00:20:52.036
I won’t get to walk to school
by myself again.

00:20:52.069 --> 00:20:54.340
This will be
my first and last chance.

00:20:56.478 --> 00:20:59.017
At least
I finally got to try it.

00:20:59.050 --> 00:21:01.556
One time is better than none.

00:21:01.589 --> 00:21:03.492
[laughter]

00:21:06.799 --> 00:21:09.237
Would have been nice
to have some company, though.

00:21:09.270 --> 00:21:11.843
[panting]

00:21:12.978 --> 00:21:14.648
[tires squeal]

00:21:16.586 --> 00:21:18.656
‐ President?!
‐ What the‐‐

00:21:18.690 --> 00:21:20.426
You should already
be at school by now!

00:21:20.459 --> 00:21:23.065
The morning bell’s gonna ring
in just a few minutes!

00:21:23.098 --> 00:21:25.737
But you’re just as late as I am.

00:21:25.770 --> 00:21:26.572
I’m not late!

00:21:26.606 --> 00:21:28.743
I haven’t been tardy
a day in my life.

00:21:28.776 --> 00:21:31.181
But there’s no way you’re
gonna make it on foot.

00:21:31.214 --> 00:21:33.485
If you were walking,
you should have left sooner!

00:21:33.520 --> 00:21:36.191
As members of
the Shuchiin Student Council,

00:21:36.224 --> 00:21:37.895
we should never be late.

00:21:37.928 --> 00:21:38.897
Hop on.

00:21:38.930 --> 00:21:40.232
We gotta book it.

00:21:40.266 --> 00:21:41.502
So we can’t be late,

00:21:41.536 --> 00:21:43.372
but it’s fine
to violate traffic laws?

00:21:43.405 --> 00:21:46.144
School rules take priority
over traffic rules in this case,

00:21:46.178 --> 00:21:47.681
so hush up and get on!

00:21:47.714 --> 00:21:49.384
[chuckles]

00:21:51.121 --> 00:21:53.025
[wheels whizzing]

00:21:57.200 --> 00:21:58.168
[gasps]

00:21:58.202 --> 00:22:00.306
[peaceful music playing]

00:22:10.560 --> 00:22:13.666
[narrator] <i>The cat‐tastrophe</i>
<i>was solved by the next day,</i>

00:22:13.700 --> 00:22:16.004
<i>and she returned</i>
<i>to her normal routine.</i>

00:22:16.037 --> 00:22:17.608
[laughter]

00:22:17.641 --> 00:22:19.745
‐ Can I come over later?
‐ Yeah! Of course!

00:22:19.778 --> 00:22:20.714
<i>But sometimes...</i>

00:22:22.651 --> 00:22:27.728
<i>she would reminisce about</i>
<i>that special day and smile.</i>

00:22:31.101 --> 00:22:35.075
[school bells chiming]

00:22:41.822 --> 00:22:43.726
[singing in Japanese]

